4.00	Dichloro-Diphenyl-Trichloroethane	DDT	DDT (dichlorodiphenyltrichloroethane) is an organochlorine insecticide which is a white crystalline solid, tasteless and almost odourless. Technical DDT has been formulated in almost every conceivable form including solutions in xylene or petroleum distillates, emulsifiable concentrates, water-wettable powders, granules, aerosols, smoke candles, charges for vaporisers and lotions.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0b/P%2Cp%27-dichlorodiphenyltrichloroethane.svg/200px-P%2Cp%27-dichlorodiphenyltrichloroethane.svg.png
